WEBVTT

00:00:01.650 --> 00:00:13.890
In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful.

00:00:17.890 --> 00:00:21.360
Par excellence presents

00:00:30.190 --> 00:00:32.190
Lessons from the stories of the prophets

00:00:37.190 --> 00:00:39.190
by Mufti Ismail ibn Musa Menk

00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:47.920
Creation of Adam,

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:50.920
Creation of Adam, Peace be upon him.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
All praises due to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:10.000
blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:14.000
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to bless him and to bless every single one of us.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:20.000
And we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to accept from us the first fast that we have fasted.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:26.000
And we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to accept from us the second tarwihah that we have engaged in.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:30.000
As I said, it comes with a lot of sacrifice.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.000
The month of Ramadan is a month of sacrifice.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:40.000
And it comes with really a lot of self-discipline and control.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.000
We cannot eat what we want.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:46.000
In fact, we will not eat anything through the day.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:51.000
And outside Ramadan, we would be grateful to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to say,

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
If we could abstain from that which was permissible for your sake,

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:01.000
then to abstain from that which is prohibited is far more simple by the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:08.000
And also if we can engage in 20 extra rakaat as is the case here with us,

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:11.000
for the sake of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.000
then the five daily salawat is not much.

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.000
We ask Allah to grant us strength.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:17.000
And we ask Allah to open our doors.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:21.000
For indeed, this is a month where it is said,

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:27.000
O you who wants goodness, come forward.

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:30.000
And O you who intends evil, go back.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:35.000
So anyone who wants goodness, Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala draws them closer and closer in this month.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.000
This evening, I will continue from where I left off last night.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:45.000
And as you know, it was the introduction of the series that we have commenced with.

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:54.000
And I had ended where we were making mention of why is it that the stories of the previous prophets are made mention of.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.000
And I made mention of one point and I'd like to go further.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:05.000
But before I do that, it is important for us to highlight where we got the word stories from.

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Sometimes it does not sound appropriate to use the word stories when it comes to the Quran.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:13.000
Rather we'd say the lives of the prophets.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:15.000
Someone might say we'd rather say something else.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:18.000
But if you look at the words used in the Quran,

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:22.000
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says to Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:35.000
So narrate to them the qasas, the stories, in order that they may ponder.

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:38.000
So these stories are narrated to us for what reason?

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.000
That we may ponder and we may learn a thing or two.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:45.000
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was told in the Quran,

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:55.000
You were not there, O Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:59.000
At that mount when we called out to Musa alayhi salatu was salam.

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:01.000
But how did you know about it?

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:03.000
We informed you about it.

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:07.000
We are fortunate that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has informed us as well about it.

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
As I said yesterday, if it was not for revelation, we would never know what it was.

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:16.000
So we have selected the word stories because it is the closest.

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:20.000
In fact in surah Yusuf Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says right at the beginning,

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:38.000
We are narrating to you the best of stories in that which we have revealed in this Quran.

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:40.000
So that is the best of stories.

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:42.000
So Allah calls it a story.

00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:48.000
Now if we look at why or some of the other reasons that these stories are made mention of,

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:56.000
It is in order to be a consolation and a comfort to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam and to anyone who wants to carry out that work.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:00.000
What does this mean? Allah says in the Quran,

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:27.000
And each time we mention for you a story of those of the past,

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:34.000
It is in order to comfort you, to grant you strength, to strengthen you, to be a form of consolation for you.

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:40.000
When you know the stories of the past, you will be able to relate to what is happening now in your midst.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:45.000
And indeed in this Quran, the truth has come as a reminder for those who believe.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:49.000
So we ask Allah to grant us a reminder from these particular stories.

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:53.000
Now let us commence from the beginning of creation.

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:57.000
Right at the beginning, Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala created the pen.

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.000
And he told the pen, write whatever is going to happen up to the end.

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:04.000
That was the instruction of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:08.000
How exactly it happened? We do not need to know.

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:10.000
Why do we say we do not need to know?

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:15.000
Because there are certain things that our brains and our minds are incapable of understanding.

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:17.000
We will never be able to understand.

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:22.000
In the same way that the other creatures have a brain according to their capacity,

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:28.000
And they feel that they are sophisticated, and they feel that they have improved, so does man.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.000
Man feels he is so improved and he has eyes.

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:35.000
Can you see what we call the unseen? The answer is no.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.000
We believe that they are jinn kind. Can we see them? The answer is no.

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:41.000
We believe the angels come and go. Can we see them? The answer is no.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:46.000
Which means our eyes are restricted to a restriction placed by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:51.000
So there are certain things, if they are not in the Quran, we will not need to know them.

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
If they are not in the correct sunnah of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam, we will not need to know them.

00:06:57.000 --> 00:07:02.000
However, there are certain narrations known as riwayat Israeliyah.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:05.000
The Israeli riwayat. Who is Israel?

00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:08.000
Who is Israel? Israel is the prophet Jacob, may peace be upon him.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:11.000
He was also known as Israel, Yaqoob a.s.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
Now there are narrations that have come to us via the people of the book,

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:22.000
more so the Jewish clans and tribes who were there at the time of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam and before.

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:25.000
So those narrations, how do we treat them?

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:28.000
Because we find them, people have read them, and as I said yesterday,

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:31.000
there are some similarities between all these revelations.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:34.000
There are three types of these narrations.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:39.000
First, those which the Quran or the sunnah have negated and disagreed with,

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:42.000
those we would throw them out completely.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:50.000
Secondly, those which the Quran has confirmed or the sunnah of the prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam has confirmed,

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:55.000
those we will take them, not because they were found in the riwayat Israeliyah,

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:01.000
but because they were found in our narrations and they were found to be in conformance with what the prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam brought.

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:06.000
And the third type of narrations are those where the Quran has not said anything,

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:10.000
the sunnah has not said anything about it, it is not negated, nor is it confirmed.

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:13.000
For those, we have a policy. We say,

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:18.000
we neither believe it nor do we disbelieve it.

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:22.000
We hold it, we might read it, it might create a little bit of information in our minds,

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:24.000
but we neither believe nor reject it.

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:28.000
We do not actually need to know those details.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.000
So this is something very important.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.000
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala created the angels,

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:35.000
and then He created the jinn kind.

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:40.000
Very interestingly, He created another kind known as the bin kind.

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:43.000
Ibn Kathir rahimahullah makes mention of this in one of his books,

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
Al bidayah wa nihayah, which is the book that I have mainly used for this series as well.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:55.000
So he says in there that there was a certain creature or creatures of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala known as bin, the bin.

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:57.000
And they were on the earth.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:00.000
And on the earth, they created chaos and havoc and so on.

00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:04.000
Allah sent the jinn to deal with the bin on earth.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:07.000
So the jinn came in and they dealt with the bin,

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:11.000
and they overcame them and overpowered them and destroyed them completely.

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:13.000
And who was the head of the jinn?

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.000
One known as Iblis.

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:17.000
One known as Iblis.

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:19.000
So he was very, very proud of his good deed.

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:22.000
This is why we say a lesson drawn from this.

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:26.000
Whenever you do a good deed, don't let it make you arrogant and think I'm holy.

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:28.000
I'm pious. The other one is nothing.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:31.000
No, we do not judge books by their covers, number one.

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.000
And number two, no matter what level you are on,

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:38.000
look at those who are above you and tell yourself I have not got anywhere yet.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:40.000
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:44.000
And there is a chance that those who might appear to be lower than us,

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:49.000
they might overtake us along, meaning very, very far.

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:51.000
They will be ahead of us at some stage.

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:54.000
So if we are to talk about them thinking that these people are below us,

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:57.000
who knows Allah might create a day when they will overtake us.

00:09:58.000 --> 00:09:59.000
So what happened to Iblis?

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:01.000
He became very proud. He was so happy.

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:03.000
So happy that whenever the people,

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:05.000
whenever those in the heavens were addressed,

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:07.000
he was addressed as one of them.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:09.000
He used to be addressed as the angels.

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:11.000
You know, I like to give the example of a donkey.

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:14.000
And I say when people have come to visit you,

00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:18.000
the whole community came and they came riding on their donkeys.

00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:21.000
You say the community came to visit us,

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:23.000
but you didn't say their donkeys also came.

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:25.000
Because the donkey is part of the community.

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:27.000
It's come and it's now come to you.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:29.000
So don't make mention of it.

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:31.000
So when Allah speaks of Malaika,

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:33.000
Iblis was also included in it.

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:36.000
Iblis was also included in it,

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:38.000
but he was not from amongst them.

00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:41.000
He was just included because he happened to be a good person.

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:43.000
Like nowadays we say, oh, he's such an angel,

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:45.000
or she is such an angel and so on.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:47.000
Do we really mean they have joined the ranks of Jibreel?

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:49.000
The answer is no.

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:51.000
But what we mean is they are very good and so on.

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:53.000
So he was good at the time.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:56.000
Then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala thereafter informed the angels

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:58.000
of something very important in Surah Al-Baqarah.

00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:00.000
Imagine right at the beginning of the Quran,

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:02.000
Allah is speaking about it very interestingly.

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:13.000
And remember when Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:18.000
your Rabb told the angels that I am creating a Khalifa on the earth.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:20.000
I am creating a Khalifa on the earth.

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:22.000
What is the meaning of a Khalifa?

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:25.000
It has two meanings, two important meanings.

00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:29.000
One who stands in the place of someone else

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:34.000
or one who assumes the position of another, important.

00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:36.000
So that is the first meaning, Khalifa.

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:40.000
They say this person is a Khalifa of Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:42.000
that was Abu Bakr, al-Siddiq radiallahu anhu.

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:44.000
They called him Khulafa,

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:46.000
those who came and assumed the position of the other

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:48.000
and they continued the work.

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:50.000
So that is the first meaning.

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:52.000
The second is more appropriate.

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:53.000
One who succeeds another,

00:11:54.000 --> 00:11:56.000
those who come succeeding one after the other.

00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:58.000
So think about it carefully.

00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:00.000
The angels, they don't die.

00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:03.000
The jinn kind, Allah knows, but they live very long.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:05.000
They don't succeed.

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:07.000
They actually live very long.

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:09.000
But everything on earth, what happens to it?

00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:11.000
It has a life span and it continues.

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:13.000
Adam alayhi salam came

00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:15.000
and after a while his children continued.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:17.000
He was gone.

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:19.000
His children went and others came.

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:21.000
Then they were gone and their children died.

00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:23.000
Their children came.

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:25.000
We are here.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:27.000
We will go after a while.

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:29.000
So we are only here for a period of time.

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:31.000
This is also known as Khalifa,

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:33.000
one who succeeds another.

00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:35.000
We have succeeded those before us

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:37.000
and those after us will succeed us.

00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:39.000
That is also the meaning of Khalifa.

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:41.000
So when Allah says,

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:43.000
I am putting on the earth a Khalifa,

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:45.000
it would also mean

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:47.000
those who are coming one after the other,

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:49.000
they will not last until the end of the earth,

00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:51.000
but they will come one after the other.

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:53.000
They said,

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.000
Oh Allah, are you going to create someone

00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:10.000
and place them on earth

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:12.000
who are going to cause chaos

00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:14.000
and they are going to spill blood

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:16.000
and they are going to do a lot of damage on the earth

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:18.000
and yet we are here,

00:13:19.000 --> 00:13:20.000
we are declaring your praise,

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:21.000
Allah says,

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:27.000
I know that which you do not know.

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:29.000
Knowledge is with Allah.

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:32.000
Allah had a purpose to create Adam.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:35.000
It is important for us to know this purpose

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:37.000
and aim because we have succeeded them.

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:39.000
We are now on earth.

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:43.000
Adam is no longer alive here with us.

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:45.000
So we need to know why we were created.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:47.000
So Allah continues.

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:49.000
This discussion is so beautiful.

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:52.000
It is mentioned in Surah Al-Baqarah

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:54.000
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:56.000
thereafter that He created Adam.

00:13:57.000 --> 00:13:58.000
Let us spend a few moments,

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:00.000
how He created Adam,

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:02.000
the Quran uses several words.

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:04.000
It uses the word Turab,

00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:06.000
it uses the word Teen,

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:08.000
it uses the word Salsal,

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:10.000
it uses the word Hama im Masnoon.

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:12.000
What are these words?

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:14.000
One is dust, one is soil,

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:17.000
one is clay and one is the dark clay.

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:19.000
So why all these words are used

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:21.000
and it is depicting different stages

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:23.000
in the creation of man.

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:25.000
Let us move further.

00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:27.000
Amazingly and interestingly,

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:30.000
Allah took dust from the earth

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:32.000
and that dust was taken from

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:34.000
different parts of the earth

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:36.000
and you and I know that the soil on the earth

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:38.000
is different colors.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:40.000
You have red, you have slightly lighter color,

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:42.000
you have a darker color,

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:44.000
you have different shades of brown and so on.

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:46.000
So there were different shades and different colors

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:49.000
and He took these from different parts of the globe

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:51.000
from the valleys, from the mountain tops,

00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:53.000
from the sandy regions,

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:55.000
from the rocky regions and so on

00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:57.000
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala put it all together.

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:00.000
This is why in mankind,

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:03.000
nowadays we use the word Jeans,

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:05.000
not referring to those hipsters that people wear.

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:08.000
No, the Jeans within man,

00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:10.000
what do we understand?

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:12.000
If it is in your Jeans,

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:14.000
if something is in your Jeans,

00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:16.000
there is a likelihood that it will be passed on to your children, hereditary.

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.000
So Adam was created from

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:22.000
different types, different colors and different qualities.

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:24.000
So from his progeny,

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:26.000
there are different colors

00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:28.000
and there are people who are easy to get along with,

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:30.000
people who are very difficult to get along with,

00:15:31.000 --> 00:15:32.000
people who are hard core, strong, powerful

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:34.000
and people who are weaklings.

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:37.000
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us the middle path

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:40.000
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us from amongst the best.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:44.000
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala created all of them so differently

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:46.000
and this is why we have different colors

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:48.000
and this is why we have different shades,

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:51.000
different attitudes and different characteristics and characters.

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:53.000
We ask Allah to grant us the best of all

00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:56.000
and we ask Allah to open the doors for us and our offspring

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:59.000
and we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to have mercy on us at all times.

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:04.000
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala then speaks about how He created this man.

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:07.000
Do you know that the narrations make mention of

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:10.000
the fact that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala first

00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:13.000
had this dust and then He added water to it,

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:16.000
it became soil and then He shaped it up,

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:18.000
it became clay and He left it.

00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:23.000
He left it for a while and then He speaks about

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:26.000
the word used in the Quran is

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.000
meaning the pottery, the clay of pottery.

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:32.000
Why does He say similar to the clay of pottery

00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:34.000
but not exactly the clay of pottery?

00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:37.000
Because for the clay of pottery, heat is used.

00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:40.000
For man, no heat was used, subhanallah.

00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:42.000
No heat was used.

00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:44.000
So if Allah said the clay of pottery,

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:45.000
it would mean heat was used

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:48.000
but He says similar to that clay of pottery

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:50.000
because there is one thing missing.

00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:52.000
Allahu Akbar.

00:16:53.000 --> 00:16:54.000
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala thereafter,

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:56.000
He left man.

00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:58.000
Now what was the size of Adam alayhi salatu was salam?

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:00.000
Very interestingly the narration says

00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:03.000
60 feet.

00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:05.000
Now what is a foot?

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:08.000
A foot one would say is about roughly from your elbow

00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:10.000
to the top or to the wrist and so on.

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:12.000
Someone might say roughly 30 centimeters.

00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:15.000
However, maybe the feet at that time might have been one meter.

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:17.000
So He was either 60 meters

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:19.000
or He was either, if we were to calculate it

00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:22.000
with today's feet, 18 meters.

00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:24.000
Either way, He was huge.

00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:26.000
Just imagine Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:28.000
created Adam alayhi salatu was salam

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:30.000
and the hadith says

00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:36.000
Allah created Adam upon his image.

00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:38.000
Now what is meant by this?

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:41.000
Ask the Christians, they will give you a totally wrong answer.

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:44.000
They will tell you it means man was created on the image of God.

00:17:45.000 --> 00:17:46.000
Astaghfirullah, that is wrong.

00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:48.000
It is simple to understand.

00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:51.000
When me and you were born, how were we created?

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:53.000
A little seed began to multiply

00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:56.000
and thereafter the form was given slowly but surely.

00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.000
But with Adam alayhi salam it was different.

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.000
Allah created him on his image from day one,

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.000
which means he was already big,

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:05.000
he already had size, he already had eyes.

00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:08.000
That is the meaning of creation in his image,

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:10.000
not the image of Allah.

00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:12.000
But Adam was created in the image of Adam,

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:14.000
wholly in those meters.

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:17.000
He was already an adult when he was created.

00:18:19.380 --> 00:18:20.380
So this is the meaning of it.

00:18:21.380 --> 00:18:22.380
We must never be confused and think that

00:18:23.380 --> 00:18:24.380
you know they say Jesus came in the form of God.

00:18:25.380 --> 00:18:26.380
Astaghfirullah, that is totally wrong.

00:18:27.380 --> 00:18:28.380
It is a mistake.

00:18:29.380 --> 00:18:30.380
According to us, we cannot discuss that matter

00:18:31.380 --> 00:18:32.380
with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:18:33.380 --> 00:18:34.380
because we would need to see Him and none of us have.

00:18:35.380 --> 00:18:36.380
So when it comes to Adam alayhi salatu was salam,

00:18:37.380 --> 00:18:38.380
Allah left him.

00:18:39.380 --> 00:18:40.380
And when Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala left him

00:18:41.380 --> 00:18:43.380
he had a certain very, very pious,

00:18:44.380 --> 00:18:46.380
very pious being who was known as Iblis,

00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:48.380
who happened to think now why is Allah doing this?

00:18:49.380 --> 00:18:50.380
You know I went on the earth

00:18:51.380 --> 00:18:52.380
and I sorted things out on the earth

00:18:53.380 --> 00:18:54.380
and I went to engage in such great acts of worship

00:18:55.380 --> 00:18:57.380
and here we have Allah creating someone else.

00:18:58.380 --> 00:18:59.380
So he began to look up and down

00:19:00.380 --> 00:19:02.380
and he is literally monitoring this creature

00:19:03.380 --> 00:19:05.380
and he is trying to look and see and survey

00:19:06.380 --> 00:19:07.380
and take a look at what is happening

00:19:08.380 --> 00:19:09.380
and he has seen the size and he has seen the belly,

00:19:09.380 --> 00:19:10.380
he has seen the stomach.

00:19:11.380 --> 00:19:12.380
One narration says when he checked its hollow,

00:19:13.380 --> 00:19:15.380
he says oh, I know I can control this.

00:19:16.380 --> 00:19:17.380
I know.

00:19:18.380 --> 00:19:19.380
Do you know what that means?

00:19:20.380 --> 00:19:21.380
He is not consistent.

00:19:22.380 --> 00:19:23.380
This man will not be consistent.

00:19:24.380 --> 00:19:25.380
We will be able to push him this way or that way.

00:19:26.380 --> 00:19:27.380
And he already made a promise.

00:19:28.380 --> 00:19:30.380
Before the rooh or the soul was blown

00:19:31.380 --> 00:19:32.380
into Adam alayhi salam,

00:19:33.380 --> 00:19:34.380
you find Iblis making a promise.

00:19:35.380 --> 00:19:36.380
He looks at this,

00:19:37.380 --> 00:19:38.380
this more or less a statue

00:19:39.380 --> 00:19:40.380
of Iblis lying

00:19:41.380 --> 00:19:42.380
and he says no.

00:19:43.380 --> 00:19:44.380
If I have an opportunity,

00:19:45.380 --> 00:19:46.380
I am going to lead you astray

00:19:47.380 --> 00:19:48.380
and if you are made to be higher than me,

00:19:49.380 --> 00:19:50.380
I will never follow you.

00:19:51.380 --> 00:19:52.380
This is what Iblis says.

00:19:53.380 --> 00:19:54.380
From that time, what was the sin?

00:19:55.380 --> 00:19:56.380
The sin was he thought he was too holy.

00:19:57.380 --> 00:19:58.380
This is what it is.

00:19:59.380 --> 00:20:00.380
This is why let us be careful.

00:20:01.380 --> 00:20:02.380
When Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has granted us

00:20:03.380 --> 00:20:04.380
the acceptance to fulfill salah,

00:20:05.380 --> 00:20:06.380
let's not think we are doing him a favor.

00:20:07.380 --> 00:20:08.380
Wallahi we are doing ourselves a favor

00:20:09.380 --> 00:20:11.380
who knows that person might be sacrificing

00:20:12.380 --> 00:20:13.380
much more than us in a different way

00:20:14.380 --> 00:20:16.380
and they might be closer to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala than us.

00:20:17.380 --> 00:20:18.380
So this issue of becoming too holy

00:20:19.380 --> 00:20:20.380
or feeling that I am it,

00:20:21.380 --> 00:20:22.380
what does it make us do?

00:20:23.380 --> 00:20:24.380
May Allah protect us.

00:20:25.380 --> 00:20:26.380
It might make us look at others with an inferiority

00:20:27.380 --> 00:20:29.380
meaning that they are inferior to us.

00:20:30.380 --> 00:20:32.380
We would have a superiority complex so to speak.

00:20:33.380 --> 00:20:34.380
May Allah protect us.

00:20:35.380 --> 00:20:36.380
That's what happened to Iblis.

00:20:37.380 --> 00:20:38.380
So when Iblis looked at this,

00:20:39.380 --> 00:20:40.380
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala began

00:20:41.380 --> 00:20:46.380
or he blew the soul into Adam alayhi salatu was salam.

00:20:47.380 --> 00:20:48.380
And where did it start from?

00:20:49.380 --> 00:20:51.380
Very interestingly, it started from the top, from the head.

00:20:52.380 --> 00:20:57.380
So the most honored organ that we have is the brain.

00:20:58.380 --> 00:21:00.380
That is what distinguishes us from the rest of creatures.

00:21:01.380 --> 00:21:02.380
We have a brain.

00:21:03.380 --> 00:21:04.380
Allah gave it life first before everything else.

00:21:05.380 --> 00:21:06.380
Then as the soul came,

00:21:07.380 --> 00:21:08.380
meaning as the life began to come,

00:21:09.380 --> 00:21:10.380
it was turning into flesh and blood.

00:21:11.380 --> 00:21:13.380
From soil, it was becoming flesh and blood.

00:21:14.380 --> 00:21:15.380
And the brain came alive.

00:21:16.380 --> 00:21:18.380
Then the eyes came alive and Adam alayhi salatu was salam

00:21:19.380 --> 00:21:20.380
suddenly opened his eyes.

00:21:21.380 --> 00:21:22.380
Imagine what must have happened.

00:21:23.380 --> 00:21:24.380
An adult opening his eyes,

00:21:25.380 --> 00:21:26.380
granted full knowledge.

00:21:27.380 --> 00:21:28.380
Allah says in the Quran,

00:21:29.380 --> 00:21:35.380
We taught Adam alayhi salam the names of everything.

00:21:36.380 --> 00:21:38.380
So we brought everything that was in creation

00:21:39.380 --> 00:21:41.380
and we told him this is a tree, this is a stone,

00:21:42.380 --> 00:21:43.380
this is a mountain, so on.

00:21:44.380 --> 00:21:45.380
So he was already taught.

00:21:46.380 --> 00:21:47.380
He was not like us when you born

00:21:48.380 --> 00:21:49.380
and then you slowly learn and you learn to say Allah

00:21:50.380 --> 00:21:51.380
and then you learn to say something else

00:21:52.380 --> 00:21:53.380
and then you learn to say daddy and mommy.

00:21:54.380 --> 00:21:56.380
No, it was not like that with Adam alayhi salatu was salam.

00:21:57.380 --> 00:21:59.380
He already knew the words and the names of everything.

00:22:00.380 --> 00:22:02.380
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala speaks about that in the Quran.

00:22:03.380 --> 00:22:04.380
So as his eyes opened,

00:22:05.380 --> 00:22:06.380
he saw the fruits of Jannah.

00:22:07.380 --> 00:22:08.380
He was in Jannah.

00:22:09.380 --> 00:22:10.380
He didn't know.

00:22:11.380 --> 00:22:12.380
We haven't been in yet.

00:22:13.380 --> 00:22:14.380
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us paradise.

00:22:15.380 --> 00:22:16.380
So when his eyes opened, he was so happy.

00:22:17.380 --> 00:22:18.380
He seen all his fruits and so on.

00:22:19.380 --> 00:22:20.380
He already understood what it was.

00:22:21.380 --> 00:22:23.380
And what happened as the soul was blown

00:22:24.380 --> 00:22:26.380
and it was the life came into his nose and his mouth,

00:22:27.380 --> 00:22:28.380
he sneezed.

00:22:29.380 --> 00:22:31.380
So sneezing is a sign of goodness.

00:22:32.380 --> 00:22:33.380
It is a gift of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:22:34.380 --> 00:22:35.380
which protects you from illness.

00:22:36.380 --> 00:22:37.380
There is a sneeze.

00:22:37.380 --> 00:22:40.380
So one narration says the angel said,

00:22:41.380 --> 00:22:43.380
Oh Adam, thank Allah.

00:22:44.380 --> 00:22:45.380
So Adam alayhi salatu was salam says,

00:22:46.380 --> 00:22:47.380
Alhamdulillah.

00:22:48.380 --> 00:22:49.380
He says, Alhamdulillah.

00:22:50.380 --> 00:22:51.380
All praise is due to Allah.

00:22:52.380 --> 00:22:53.380
This is where we get it from.

00:22:54.380 --> 00:22:55.380
When you sneeze, you should utter all praise is due to Allah.

00:22:56.380 --> 00:22:59.380
So the narration makes mention of how Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:23:00.380 --> 00:23:03.380
responded to him that Allah has had mercy on you, oh Adam.

00:23:04.380 --> 00:23:05.380
Hence, what happens?

00:23:05.380 --> 00:23:07.380
When we hear, when we sneeze, we say Alhamdulillah.

00:23:08.380 --> 00:23:09.380
If we hear someone say Alhamdulillah,

00:23:10.380 --> 00:23:11.380
we should say, Yerhamuk Allah.

00:23:12.380 --> 00:23:14.380
We should say Allah has definitely had mercy on you.

00:23:15.380 --> 00:23:17.380
That is the beauty and this is where it started

00:23:18.380 --> 00:23:19.380
and this is where it came from.

00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:21.380
So as life came into his hands,

00:23:22.380 --> 00:23:24.380
he stretched out to get what?

00:23:25.380 --> 00:23:26.380
Amazing, amazing.

00:23:27.380 --> 00:23:28.380
He stretched out to get what?

00:23:29.380 --> 00:23:30.380
What he was seeing.

00:23:31.380 --> 00:23:32.380
He was seeing the fruits of Jannah.

00:23:33.380 --> 00:23:34.380
So he is stretching out, but life had not yet come

00:23:35.380 --> 00:23:36.380
to his legs.

00:23:37.380 --> 00:23:38.380
So he couldn't get there.

00:23:39.380 --> 00:23:40.380
And this is why the Quran says,

00:23:41.380 --> 00:23:45.380
And in another place Allah says,

00:23:50.380 --> 00:23:53.380
Man was always in a rush, always making haste.

00:23:54.380 --> 00:23:55.380
Look at us, how do we treat life?

00:23:56.380 --> 00:23:58.380
Life is like this much, so to speak,

00:23:59.380 --> 00:24:00.380
from this point to that point.

00:24:01.380 --> 00:24:02.380
And we try to get as much as we can

00:24:03.380 --> 00:24:04.380
between this point and that point.

00:24:05.380 --> 00:24:06.380
As much money, as much knowledge,

00:24:07.380 --> 00:24:08.380
as much this, as much that,

00:24:09.380 --> 00:24:10.380
let us hope that we as Muslimin

00:24:11.380 --> 00:24:12.380
can get as much Taraweeh into there

00:24:13.380 --> 00:24:14.380
and as much Quran into there

00:24:15.380 --> 00:24:16.380
and as much sacrifice into there

00:24:17.380 --> 00:24:18.380
and as much obedience of Allah into there

00:24:19.380 --> 00:24:20.380
so that by the time we get to the other point,

00:24:21.380 --> 00:24:22.380
we can be granted entry into Jannah

00:24:23.380 --> 00:24:24.380
as we mentioned yesterday.

00:24:25.380 --> 00:24:26.380
May Allah open our doors.

00:24:27.380 --> 00:24:28.380
So very beautifully Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:24:29.380 --> 00:24:30.380
makes mention of how man was always in haste.

00:24:31.380 --> 00:24:32.380
Then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:24:32.380 --> 00:24:33.380
said Adam, peace be upon him,

00:24:34.380 --> 00:24:37.380
he instructed the angels to prostrate.

00:24:38.380 --> 00:24:40.380
That prostration was not to worship him,

00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:44.380
but only in order to recognize

00:24:45.380 --> 00:24:46.380
and to acknowledge his status.

00:24:47.380 --> 00:24:49.380
His status was raised higher than all of them.

00:24:50.380 --> 00:24:53.380
So Allah says to recognize that status, prostrate.

00:25:03.380 --> 00:25:05.380
And remember when we told the angels

00:25:06.380 --> 00:25:07.380
to prostrate to Adam,

00:25:08.380 --> 00:25:09.380
they all prostrated immediately

00:25:10.380 --> 00:25:11.380
besides Iblees.

00:25:12.380 --> 00:25:13.380
Now why didn't he?

00:25:14.380 --> 00:25:15.380
Allah makes mention of it in so many places.

00:25:16.380 --> 00:25:17.380
In Surah Al-Baqarah He says

00:25:23.380 --> 00:25:25.380
He refused out of arrogance

00:25:26.380 --> 00:25:27.380
and He became from amongst those

00:25:28.380 --> 00:25:29.380
who were disbelievers.

00:25:30.380 --> 00:25:31.380
This was the first sin being committed

00:25:32.380 --> 00:25:33.380
by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:25:34.380 --> 00:25:35.380
The first sin.

00:25:36.380 --> 00:25:37.380
He refused out of arrogance.

00:25:38.380 --> 00:25:39.380
So what is the meaning of arrogance?

00:25:40.380 --> 00:25:41.380
Istikbar.

00:25:42.380 --> 00:25:43.380
The Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam says

00:25:44.380 --> 00:25:46.380
that arrogance is not when you wear good clothes

00:25:47.380 --> 00:25:48.380
or when you drive a good vehicle.

00:25:49.380 --> 00:25:50.380
No, it is when you reject the truth

00:25:51.380 --> 00:25:52.380
and you despise people.

00:25:53.380 --> 00:25:54.380
Look at that translation.

00:25:55.380 --> 00:25:56.380
So beautiful.

00:25:57.380 --> 00:25:58.380
Whenever anyone rejects the truth,

00:25:59.380 --> 00:26:00.380
they are proud, they are arrogant.

00:26:00.380 --> 00:26:01.380
Because other people, they are proud,

00:26:02.380 --> 00:26:03.380
they are arrogant.

00:26:04.380 --> 00:26:05.380
Remember those two.

00:26:06.380 --> 00:26:07.380
Because a lot of people don't understand

00:26:08.380 --> 00:26:09.380
the meaning of pride.

00:26:10.380 --> 00:26:11.380
You look at a man in good clothing

00:26:12.380 --> 00:26:13.380
and you say look at that uncle,

00:26:14.380 --> 00:26:15.380
he is proud.

00:26:16.380 --> 00:26:17.380
That statement of ours is actually pride.

00:26:18.380 --> 00:26:19.380
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:26:20.380 --> 00:26:21.380
a deeper understanding.

00:26:22.380 --> 00:26:23.380
Because the sahabah asked the Prophet

00:26:24.380 --> 00:26:25.380
salallahu alaihi wasallam

00:26:26.380 --> 00:26:27.380
that nobody will enter Jannah

00:26:28.380 --> 00:26:29.380
if they have got even a mustard

00:26:30.380 --> 00:26:31.380
weight of pride in their hearts.

00:26:32.380 --> 00:26:33.380
We like to wear good clothing.

00:26:34.380 --> 00:26:35.380
We like to have a good conveyance.

00:26:36.380 --> 00:26:37.380
The Prophet salallahu alaihi wasallam says

00:26:38.380 --> 00:26:39.380
no, that's not what is pride.

00:26:40.380 --> 00:26:41.380
Pride is when you reject the truth

00:26:42.380 --> 00:26:43.380
and when you despise people.

00:26:44.380 --> 00:26:45.380
So Iblis was the one who showed

00:26:46.380 --> 00:26:47.380
that pride and arrogance.

00:26:48.380 --> 00:26:49.380
In another place in the Quran,

00:26:50.380 --> 00:26:51.380
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:26:52.380 --> 00:26:56.380
He was from amongst the jinn kind.

00:26:57.380 --> 00:26:58.380
You see, he was not from amongst the angels.

00:26:58.380 --> 00:26:59.380
Allah says he was from amongst the jinn.

00:27:00.380 --> 00:27:01.380
Now the angels were created from noor,

00:27:02.380 --> 00:27:03.380
from light.

00:27:04.380 --> 00:27:05.380
And the jinn were created

00:27:06.380 --> 00:27:07.380
from a smokeless fire

00:27:08.380 --> 00:27:09.380
that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:27:10.380 --> 00:27:11.380
makes mention of even in surah ar-Rahman.

00:27:12.380 --> 00:27:13.380
And this is why there was a difference

00:27:14.380 --> 00:27:15.380
between them.

00:27:16.380 --> 00:27:17.380
And where did this difference show?

00:27:18.380 --> 00:27:19.380
It showed when man was created.

00:27:20.380 --> 00:27:21.380
Now the two were differentiated.

00:27:22.380 --> 00:27:23.380
And then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:27:24.380 --> 00:27:25.380
to Adam alayhi salatu wasalam.

00:27:26.380 --> 00:27:27.380
In fact, before that,

00:27:28.380 --> 00:27:29.380
Allah questions Iblis.

00:27:34.380 --> 00:27:35.380
What is it that is stopping you

00:27:36.380 --> 00:27:37.380
from prostrating to that

00:27:38.380 --> 00:27:39.380
which I have created with my own hands?

00:27:40.380 --> 00:27:41.380
Allah says.

00:27:42.380 --> 00:27:43.380
What is it that is stopping you

00:27:44.380 --> 00:27:45.380
from prostrating to this

00:27:46.380 --> 00:27:47.380
that I have created?

00:27:48.380 --> 00:27:49.380
Do you know what he says?

00:27:50.380 --> 00:27:51.380
He says,

00:27:59.380 --> 00:28:00.380
I am much better than him.

00:28:01.380 --> 00:28:02.380
You made him from dust

00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:04.380
and you made me from fire.

00:28:05.380 --> 00:28:06.380
How can I prostrate to him?

00:28:07.380 --> 00:28:08.380
He must prostrate to me.

00:28:09.380 --> 00:28:10.380
Who is he?

00:28:11.380 --> 00:28:12.380
Now let us look into our lives.

00:28:13.380 --> 00:28:14.380
As we said, we want to draw lessons from this.

00:28:15.380 --> 00:28:16.380
We don't just want to mention the history.

00:28:17.380 --> 00:28:18.380
The lesson is never underestimate

00:28:19.380 --> 00:28:20.380
the next person, never.

00:28:21.380 --> 00:28:22.380
Don't think this man is poor,

00:28:23.380 --> 00:28:24.380
this man is not good looking,

00:28:25.380 --> 00:28:26.380
this man is like this or this woman is like that

00:28:26.380 --> 00:28:27.380
and he has that so I am better.

00:28:28.380 --> 00:28:29.380
Not at all.

00:28:30.380 --> 00:28:31.380
We are taught,

00:28:33.380 --> 00:28:35.380
people are equal like the teeth of a comb.

00:28:36.380 --> 00:28:37.380
You see in a comb and its teeth,

00:28:38.380 --> 00:28:39.380
we are all equal exactly like that

00:28:40.380 --> 00:28:42.380
when it comes to access to Allah SWT.

00:28:43.380 --> 00:28:44.380
Allah loves you as much as He loves me.

00:28:45.380 --> 00:28:46.380
He is waiting for you to turn to Him

00:28:47.380 --> 00:28:48.380
as much as He is waiting for me to turn to Him.

00:28:49.380 --> 00:28:51.380
So nobody should think that no one is better than the other.

00:28:52.380 --> 00:28:53.380
May Allah SWT open our doors.

00:28:54.380 --> 00:28:55.380
And here we are speaking of

00:28:56.380 --> 00:28:57.380
our own fault.

00:28:58.380 --> 00:28:59.380
If we feel that someone is pious

00:29:00.380 --> 00:29:01.380
or someone is closer to Allah SWT,

00:29:02.380 --> 00:29:03.380
that is different.

00:29:04.380 --> 00:29:05.380
But we are talking about feeling that someone is inferior

00:29:06.380 --> 00:29:07.380
and feeling that someone is lower.

00:29:08.380 --> 00:29:09.380
May Allah SWT never ever make us from those

00:29:10.380 --> 00:29:11.380
who look down upon other people.

00:29:12.380 --> 00:29:13.380
So Allah SWT speaks about

00:29:14.380 --> 00:29:16.380
how this Iblis refused

00:29:17.380 --> 00:29:18.380
and he is debating with Allah

00:29:19.380 --> 00:29:20.380
and he told Allah SWT

00:29:20.380 --> 00:29:26.380
If you give me respect up to the day of judgment,

00:29:27.380 --> 00:29:28.380
the day when everything is going to come to an end,

00:29:29.380 --> 00:29:30.380
then I will show you.

00:29:37.380 --> 00:29:40.380
I will lead astray all that progeny that you spoke about

00:29:41.380 --> 00:29:42.380
that will follow him except a few.

00:29:43.380 --> 00:29:44.380
Who are those few?

00:29:45.380 --> 00:29:46.380
Allah SWT makes mention of them.

00:29:51.380 --> 00:29:54.380
Those who are my true worshippers,

00:29:55.380 --> 00:29:56.380
you will not have any authority over them,

00:29:57.380 --> 00:29:58.380
O Iblis.

00:29:59.380 --> 00:30:00.380
You won't be able to handle them or to control them.

00:30:01.380 --> 00:30:02.380
So let's take a look at what happened.

00:30:03.380 --> 00:30:05.380
When Adam was now standing

00:30:06.380 --> 00:30:07.380
and Allah SWT taught him all the names,

00:30:08.380 --> 00:30:11.380
Allah SWT told him to go to the angels

00:30:12.380 --> 00:30:14.380
and he was told to greet the angels.

00:30:15.380 --> 00:30:16.380
This is a narration which is correct

00:30:17.380 --> 00:30:18.380
and it is authentic in Sahih al-Bukhari.

00:30:18.380 --> 00:30:19.380
He went up to the angels

00:30:20.380 --> 00:30:21.380
as instructed by Allah SWT

00:30:22.380 --> 00:30:23.380
and he was told to tell them,

00:30:24.380 --> 00:30:25.380
Peace be upon you.

00:30:26.380 --> 00:30:28.380
When he greeted them, they greeted him back.

00:30:31.380 --> 00:30:32.380
So this is our greeting.

00:30:33.380 --> 00:30:34.380
You see where we get it from?

00:30:35.380 --> 00:30:36.380
And this is why even the previous nations

00:30:37.380 --> 00:30:39.380
or those who have the other books,

00:30:40.380 --> 00:30:41.380
the people of the book,

00:30:42.380 --> 00:30:43.380
they are also taught to greet in a similar way

00:30:44.380 --> 00:30:45.380
but a lot of them have lost it

00:30:46.380 --> 00:30:47.380
to the highs and the highs and the yos and what have you.

00:30:48.380 --> 00:30:49.380
To protect us.

00:30:50.380 --> 00:30:51.380
Yes, this is what has happened.

00:30:52.380 --> 00:30:53.380
We used to have a yo-yo when we were young.

00:30:54.380 --> 00:30:55.380
It's a little thing that goes down.

00:30:56.380 --> 00:30:57.380
After that we heard them cutting it in half

00:30:58.380 --> 00:30:59.380
and giving it to you as a greeting.

00:31:00.380 --> 00:31:01.380
May Allah open our doors.

00:31:02.380 --> 00:31:03.380
Really, we have a beautiful greeting,

00:31:04.380 --> 00:31:05.380
may peace be upon you.

00:31:06.380 --> 00:31:07.380
For your information, do you know what it means?

00:31:08.380 --> 00:31:09.380
It means I guarantee you I won't harm you.

00:31:10.380 --> 00:31:13.380
Because if I am saying may peace be upon you,

00:31:14.380 --> 00:31:15.380
from what? From my harm.

00:31:16.380 --> 00:31:17.380
So I am not going to harm you,

00:31:18.380 --> 00:31:19.380
we are friends basically.

00:31:20.380 --> 00:31:21.380
We are together.

00:31:22.380 --> 00:31:23.380
And this is why it is hypocritical

00:31:24.380 --> 00:31:25.380
to greet a person and say,

00:31:26.380 --> 00:31:27.380
peace be upon you.

00:31:28.380 --> 00:31:29.380
And then behind his back you are busy

00:31:30.380 --> 00:31:31.380
stabbing him and so on.

00:31:32.380 --> 00:31:33.380
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us.

00:31:34.380 --> 00:31:35.380
This is why in a narration

00:31:36.380 --> 00:31:37.380
the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wa sallam says,

00:31:40.380 --> 00:31:41.380
Should I not show you that

00:31:42.380 --> 00:31:43.380
which if you were to spread it properly,

00:31:44.380 --> 00:31:45.380
it would spread the peace

00:31:46.380 --> 00:31:47.380
and the love between you?

00:31:48.380 --> 00:31:49.380
What is it?

00:31:50.380 --> 00:31:51.380
The correct greeting in the proper way

00:31:52.380 --> 00:31:53.380
without hypocrisy.

00:31:54.380 --> 00:31:55.380
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:31:56.380 --> 00:31:57.380
to make us from those

00:31:58.380 --> 00:31:59.380
who can love one another

00:32:00.380 --> 00:32:01.380
solely because we share

00:32:02.380 --> 00:32:03.380
La ilaha illa Allah

00:32:04.380 --> 00:32:05.380
Muhammadur Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam.

00:32:06.380 --> 00:32:07.380
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala speaks of this

00:32:08.380 --> 00:32:09.380
and how Iblis, may the curse be upon him,

00:32:10.380 --> 00:32:11.380
already did this.

00:32:12.380 --> 00:32:13.380
Then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:32:14.380 --> 00:32:15.380
Tell those angels

00:32:16.380 --> 00:32:17.380
the names of all these things

00:32:18.380 --> 00:32:19.380
So Allah asked the angels first,

00:32:20.380 --> 00:32:21.380
do you know the names of these things?

00:32:22.380 --> 00:32:23.380
And they said, we don't know

00:32:24.380 --> 00:32:25.380
what Allah knows. Allah knows, we don't know.

00:32:26.380 --> 00:32:27.380
So Allah says,

00:32:32.380 --> 00:32:34.380
O Adam, tell them the names of these things.

00:32:35.380 --> 00:32:36.380
And Adam sallallahu alaihi wa sallam began to recite,

00:32:37.380 --> 00:32:38.380
this is a tree, this is a stone,

00:32:39.380 --> 00:32:41.380
this is a mountain, this is this, this is that.

00:32:42.380 --> 00:32:43.380
The angels were shocked.

00:32:44.380 --> 00:32:45.380
They were shocked. They were amazed.

00:32:46.380 --> 00:32:47.380
Things they didn't know,

00:32:48.380 --> 00:32:49.380
Allah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam knew.

00:32:50.380 --> 00:32:51.380
This is when they said,

00:32:52.380 --> 00:32:53.380
O Allah, you are the knower of the unseen.

00:32:54.380 --> 00:32:55.380
And Allah says, I know that which you don't know.

00:32:56.380 --> 00:32:57.380
Didn't I tell you?

00:32:58.380 --> 00:32:59.380
But there is something else

00:33:00.380 --> 00:33:01.380
that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala referred to as well

00:33:02.380 --> 00:33:03.380
when he said, I know that which you don't know.

00:33:04.380 --> 00:33:05.380
Let's get to it.

00:33:06.380 --> 00:33:07.380
Iblis was very very angry.

00:33:08.380 --> 00:33:09.380
He already made his promises.

00:33:10.380 --> 00:33:11.380
And now what happened? Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:33:11.380 --> 00:33:28.380
Arabic

00:33:29.380 --> 00:33:30.380
We told Adam sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:33:31.380 --> 00:33:34.380
that you can dwell here with your wife

00:33:35.380 --> 00:33:37.380
and you will live in Jannah with her,

00:33:38.380 --> 00:33:40.380
have what you want, eat what you want,

00:33:41.380 --> 00:33:42.380
but there is one thing

00:33:43.380 --> 00:33:44.380
that I don't want you to do

00:33:45.380 --> 00:33:46.380
and that is that tree you don't eat from it.

00:33:47.380 --> 00:33:48.380
The one tree you don't eat from it.

00:33:49.380 --> 00:33:50.380
Now one might say,

00:33:51.380 --> 00:33:52.380
well why is it that Allah decided

00:33:53.380 --> 00:33:54.380
that he wants to have prohibitions?

00:33:55.380 --> 00:33:56.380
Someone asked me, why did Allah create the pig

00:33:57.380 --> 00:33:58.380
if he doesn't want us to eat the pig?

00:33:59.380 --> 00:34:00.380
Good question.

00:34:01.380 --> 00:34:02.380
When you have a mathematics test,

00:34:03.380 --> 00:34:04.380
do they only teach you addition?

00:34:05.380 --> 00:34:06.380
You have subtraction as well.

00:34:07.380 --> 00:34:08.380
Do they only teach you multiplication?

00:34:09.380 --> 00:34:10.380
You have division as well.

00:34:11.380 --> 00:34:12.380
You are tested this way

00:34:13.380 --> 00:34:14.380
and you are tested that way.

00:34:15.380 --> 00:34:16.380
There is a different part of your spirituality

00:34:17.380 --> 00:34:18.380
that is enhanced when you engage

00:34:19.380 --> 00:34:20.380
in fulfilling the commands.

00:34:21.380 --> 00:34:22.380
And there is a different part of your spirituality

00:34:23.380 --> 00:34:25.380
that grows when you abstain from prohibitions.

00:34:26.380 --> 00:34:27.380
Allahu Akbar, that is Allah.

00:34:28.380 --> 00:34:30.380
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala kept one thing.

00:34:31.380 --> 00:34:32.380
And what we learn from this now is

00:34:33.380 --> 00:34:34.380
most of the things are permissible

00:34:35.380 --> 00:34:36.380
besides a little list.

00:34:37.380 --> 00:34:38.380
Just like there, everything was permissible

00:34:39.380 --> 00:34:40.380
besides one item.

00:34:41.380 --> 00:34:44.380
How did Hawwa or Eve, may peace be upon her,

00:34:45.380 --> 00:34:46.380
come about?

00:34:47.380 --> 00:34:48.380
It's a very interesting question

00:34:49.380 --> 00:34:50.380
and it has a beautiful answer.

00:34:51.380 --> 00:34:52.380
According to some of the narrations,

00:34:53.380 --> 00:34:54.380
Adam was the only species,

00:34:55.380 --> 00:34:56.380
the only of his kind, mankind.

00:34:57.380 --> 00:34:58.380
One, there was no one else.

00:34:59.380 --> 00:35:00.380
Naturally, he was feeling lonely.

00:35:01.380 --> 00:35:02.380
Lonely because the angels, they are so many.

00:35:03.380 --> 00:35:04.380
This, they are so many.

00:35:05.380 --> 00:35:06.380
Me, I'm only one.

00:35:07.380 --> 00:35:08.380
So he used to want company.

00:35:09.380 --> 00:35:10.380
He used to ask Allah for company.

00:35:11.380 --> 00:35:12.380
He used to ask Allah for comfort.

00:35:13.380 --> 00:35:14.380
One day when he got up,

00:35:15.380 --> 00:35:16.380
he noticed someone looking very similar to him.

00:35:17.380 --> 00:35:18.380
What do we learn from this?

00:35:19.380 --> 00:35:21.380
A woman was given to a man as a gift

00:35:22.380 --> 00:35:23.380
after great prayer.

00:35:24.380 --> 00:35:25.380
Mashallah.

00:35:26.380 --> 00:35:27.380
So we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala really

00:35:28.380 --> 00:35:29.380
to make us from those who can appreciate that

00:35:30.380 --> 00:35:31.380
and who can understand it.

00:35:32.380 --> 00:35:33.380
Because many people forget this

00:35:34.380 --> 00:35:35.380
and they don't realize

00:35:36.380 --> 00:35:37.380
that this woman was actually a gift.

00:35:38.380 --> 00:35:39.380
But let me quickly also remind the sisters,

00:35:39.380 --> 00:35:40.380
that you are like a gift, not a burden.

00:35:41.380 --> 00:35:44.170
Ameen.

00:35:45.170 --> 00:35:46.170
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:35:47.170 --> 00:35:50.170
that this Adam had Hawwa standing right next to him

00:35:51.170 --> 00:35:52.170
and the Quran says

00:35:53.170 --> 00:35:55.170
at the beginning of Surah An-Nisa,

00:35:56.170 --> 00:35:57.170
Allah makes mention of how he created a woman.

00:35:58.170 --> 00:36:00.170
And he says we created from him,

00:36:01.170 --> 00:36:02.170
meaning from Adam,

00:36:03.170 --> 00:36:04.170
his spouse, his wife,

00:36:05.170 --> 00:36:06.170
which means Hawwa.

00:36:07.170 --> 00:36:08.170
Now there are certain people who are embarrassed

00:36:09.170 --> 00:36:10.170
and they say, no, we weren't created from man.

00:36:11.170 --> 00:36:12.170
Well, why be embarrassed?

00:36:13.170 --> 00:36:15.170
We were created from dust, from soil.

00:36:16.170 --> 00:36:17.170
At least you were created from something

00:36:18.170 --> 00:36:19.170
which was already living.

00:36:20.170 --> 00:36:21.170
Subhanallah.

00:36:22.170 --> 00:36:23.170
There is nothing embarrassing.

00:36:24.170 --> 00:36:25.170
We are there right now.

00:36:26.170 --> 00:36:27.170
Let's talk of where we are now.

00:36:28.170 --> 00:36:29.170
This is history.

00:36:30.170 --> 00:36:31.170
No need to deny a Sahih hadith

00:36:32.170 --> 00:36:33.170
and no need to deny a verse of the Quran.

00:36:34.170 --> 00:36:35.170
Clearly it says this in the opening verses

00:36:36.170 --> 00:36:37.170
of Surah An-Nisa,

00:36:38.170 --> 00:36:39.170
that Allah created man

00:36:39.170 --> 00:36:40.170
and the hadith of Abu Hurairah radiallahu anhu

00:36:41.170 --> 00:36:42.170
in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:36:43.170 --> 00:36:44.170
makes mention of the rib of Adam,

00:36:45.170 --> 00:36:47.170
there is nothing wrong with being created from a rib.

00:36:48.170 --> 00:36:49.170
And when the hadith speaks about

00:36:50.170 --> 00:36:51.170
how a rib is bent

00:36:52.170 --> 00:36:53.170
and how the top of it is bent

00:36:54.170 --> 00:36:55.170
and if you try to straighten it,

00:36:56.170 --> 00:36:57.170
you might crack it.

00:36:58.170 --> 00:36:59.170
So be very, very careful how you treat your women.

00:37:00.170 --> 00:37:01.170
I think a lot of the women don't understand that hadith

00:37:02.170 --> 00:37:03.170
and they take it personally

00:37:04.170 --> 00:37:05.170
and they take it wrongly.

00:37:06.170 --> 00:37:07.170
They think it's an insult.

00:37:07.170 --> 00:37:08.170
But all it is,

00:37:09.170 --> 00:37:10.170
it is telling the men folk

00:37:11.170 --> 00:37:12.170
that be careful how you handle the women,

00:37:13.170 --> 00:37:14.170
be very kind to them,

00:37:15.170 --> 00:37:16.170
be very tolerant,

00:37:17.170 --> 00:37:18.170
and be very, very patient with them

00:37:19.170 --> 00:37:20.170
because if you want to straighten them like a pin,

00:37:21.170 --> 00:37:22.170
you might end up cracking them,

00:37:23.170 --> 00:37:24.170
which is true.

00:37:25.170 --> 00:37:26.170
You can't have your wife exactly as you want.

00:37:27.170 --> 00:37:28.170
No, no two human beings are the same.

00:37:29.170 --> 00:37:30.170
Not at all.

00:37:31.170 --> 00:37:32.170
You know when I was young,

00:37:33.170 --> 00:37:34.170
we were always told the five fingers are not the same.

00:37:35.170 --> 00:37:36.170
One day my dad came along

00:37:37.170 --> 00:37:38.170
and changed one and changed the other one

00:37:39.170 --> 00:37:40.170
and do this to the other one,

00:37:41.170 --> 00:37:42.170
then you get all of them in one line.

00:37:43.170 --> 00:37:44.170
So it means an effort is required for us to be on par.

00:37:45.170 --> 00:37:46.170
There is a give and take.

00:37:47.170 --> 00:37:48.170
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:37:49.170 --> 00:37:50.170
Then there is the issue of Iblis

00:37:51.170 --> 00:37:52.170
who thought of his plan.

00:37:53.170 --> 00:37:54.170
He was sitting in Jannah there,

00:37:55.170 --> 00:37:56.170
he's watching, he's seeing,

00:37:57.170 --> 00:37:58.170
look Allah made one prohibition.

00:37:59.170 --> 00:38:00.170
I promised Allah that I'm going to come to Adam.

00:38:01.170 --> 00:38:02.170
The thing is he knows me.

00:38:03.170 --> 00:38:04.170
And Allah warned Adam alayhi salam.

00:38:05.170 --> 00:38:06.170
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala warned him.

00:38:07.170 --> 00:38:08.170
Allah says watch out for Iblis.

00:38:09.170 --> 00:38:11.170
Let him not take you out of the goodness you are in.

00:38:19.930 --> 00:38:21.930
Be careful that he doesn't take you out

00:38:22.930 --> 00:38:23.930
from all this goodness that you have in this garden here

00:38:24.930 --> 00:38:25.930
because then you will be unfortunate.

00:38:26.930 --> 00:38:27.930
You will be very unfortunate if you fall into his trap.

00:38:28.930 --> 00:38:29.930
Allah says,

00:38:29.930 --> 00:38:36.930
Arabic

00:38:37.930 --> 00:38:38.930
You will neither be hungry in it,

00:38:40.930 --> 00:38:41.930
nor will you ever need clothing.

00:38:42.930 --> 00:38:43.930
You won't be naked in Jannah.

00:38:44.930 --> 00:38:45.930
Nor will you ever be thirsty.

00:38:46.930 --> 00:38:47.930
And you will never ever get tired.

00:38:48.930 --> 00:38:49.930
There is nothing.

00:38:50.930 --> 00:38:51.930
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:38:52.930 --> 00:38:53.930
enjoy, enjoy as much as you want.

00:38:54.930 --> 00:38:55.930
The only thing I want you to do is make sure

00:38:56.930 --> 00:38:57.930
that you've understood the enmity

00:38:57.930 --> 00:38:58.930
that this one has against you.

00:38:59.930 --> 00:39:00.930
The enmity that this one has against you.

00:39:01.930 --> 00:39:02.930
Understand it and he has promised

00:39:03.930 --> 00:39:04.930
he's going to lead you astray.

00:39:05.930 --> 00:39:06.930
Be careful.

00:39:07.930 --> 00:39:08.930
So now one day Iblis goes after some time.

00:39:09.930 --> 00:39:10.930
He goes to Adam.

00:39:11.930 --> 00:39:12.930
And he says,

00:39:13.930 --> 00:39:18.930
Arabic

00:39:19.930 --> 00:39:20.930
Look at what plan he used.

00:39:21.930 --> 00:39:22.930
He says, oh Adam, can I show you the tree

00:39:23.930 --> 00:39:24.930
that if you eat from it,

00:39:25.930 --> 00:39:26.930
you won't die.

00:39:27.930 --> 00:39:28.930
You will have life forever.

00:39:29.930 --> 00:39:31.930
And you will have lots and lots of belongings

00:39:32.930 --> 00:39:33.930
that will never stop.

00:39:34.930 --> 00:39:35.930
You will own absolutely everything.

00:39:36.930 --> 00:39:37.930
Arabic

00:39:38.930 --> 00:39:39.930
You will have so much kingdom

00:39:40.930 --> 00:39:41.930
that it won't even finish.

00:39:42.930 --> 00:39:43.930
So Adam turned to him.

00:39:44.930 --> 00:39:45.930
That's the mistake.

00:39:46.930 --> 00:39:47.930
You don't turn to shaitan.

00:39:48.930 --> 00:39:49.930
Allah says in the Quran,

00:39:50.930 --> 00:39:56.930
Arabic

00:39:57.930 --> 00:39:59.930
When you feel the slight whisper of shaitan,

00:40:00.930 --> 00:40:01.930
immediately seek the protection of Allah

00:40:02.930 --> 00:40:03.930
against shaitan.

00:40:04.930 --> 00:40:05.930
When you feel the whisper,

00:40:06.930 --> 00:40:07.930
don't even have bad company.

00:40:08.930 --> 00:40:09.930
Don't even go in that direction.

00:40:10.930 --> 00:40:11.930
Don't even want to listen to him.

00:40:12.930 --> 00:40:13.930
Immediately throw it out and say,

00:40:14.930 --> 00:40:15.930
Arabic

00:40:16.930 --> 00:40:17.930
This is what Allah says.

00:40:18.930 --> 00:40:19.930
So Iblis managed to get the ear of Adam

00:40:20.930 --> 00:40:21.930
and Adam heard it.

00:40:22.930 --> 00:40:23.930
And he tried again.

00:40:24.930 --> 00:40:25.930
And he tried a third time and a fourth time.

00:40:25.930 --> 00:40:28.930
He decided together with his wife

00:40:29.930 --> 00:40:30.930
that now let's just have a taste of it.

00:40:31.930 --> 00:40:32.930
What are we going to lose? We have a taste.

00:40:33.930 --> 00:40:34.930
Why? Because he now had forgotten

00:40:35.930 --> 00:40:36.930
that it was prohibited.

00:40:37.930 --> 00:40:38.930
Where do we get this from?

00:40:39.930 --> 00:40:40.930
The Quran says,

00:40:41.930 --> 00:40:45.930
Arabic

00:40:46.930 --> 00:40:48.930
And we had made a promise with Adam before.

00:40:49.930 --> 00:40:50.930
But he forgot about it.

00:40:51.930 --> 00:40:53.930
And we did not find him to be resolute.

00:40:53.930 --> 00:40:54.930
Resolute.

00:40:55.930 --> 00:40:56.930
What is the meaning of resolute?

00:40:57.930 --> 00:40:58.930
He did not make a firm intention to sin

00:40:59.930 --> 00:41:00.930
and to transgress against Allah.

00:41:01.930 --> 00:41:02.930
We found when he did what he did,

00:41:03.930 --> 00:41:04.930
it was not intentional.

00:41:05.930 --> 00:41:06.930
He made a mistake.

00:41:07.930 --> 00:41:08.930
It's clear in the Quran.

00:41:09.930 --> 00:41:10.930
This is why yesterday I said that

00:41:11.930 --> 00:41:12.930
the prophets of Allah,

00:41:13.930 --> 00:41:14.930
they did not intentionally commit sin.

00:41:15.930 --> 00:41:16.930
They did not commit sin.

00:41:17.930 --> 00:41:18.930
They were protected by Allah.

00:41:19.930 --> 00:41:20.930
In the case of Adam,

00:41:21.930 --> 00:41:22.930
there's a hadith in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:41:23.930 --> 00:41:24.930
which is small.

00:41:25.930 --> 00:41:26.930
He says,

00:41:27.930 --> 00:41:28.930
You, Allah has spoken to you

00:41:29.930 --> 00:41:30.930
and He has chosen you to be spoken to.

00:41:31.930 --> 00:41:32.930
You went to kill that man.

00:41:33.930 --> 00:41:36.850
You're talking about me.

00:41:37.850 --> 00:41:38.850
How can you blame me for something

00:41:39.850 --> 00:41:40.850
that Allah had already decreed

00:41:41.850 --> 00:41:42.850
prior to my creation

00:41:43.850 --> 00:41:44.850
and He made it part of my creation

00:41:45.850 --> 00:41:46.850
for me to get onto the earth?

00:41:47.850 --> 00:41:48.850
And Musa was quiet.

00:41:49.850 --> 00:41:50.850
That is a narration in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:41:51.850 --> 00:41:52.850
that is made mention of.

00:41:53.850 --> 00:41:54.850
So we don't blame Adam,

00:41:55.850 --> 00:41:56.850
we blame Allah for what he did

00:41:57.850 --> 00:41:58.850
in order for him to come onto the earth.

00:41:59.850 --> 00:42:00.850
A question that comes up.

00:42:01.850 --> 00:42:02.850
Many people think that it was Eve.

00:42:03.850 --> 00:42:04.850
It was Hawwa,

00:42:05.850 --> 00:42:06.850
may peace be upon her,

00:42:07.850 --> 00:42:08.850
who was the one whom Satan had conned.

00:42:09.850 --> 00:42:10.850
There is no evidence for that.

00:42:11.850 --> 00:42:12.850
That is just something that people say

00:42:13.850 --> 00:42:14.850
in order to try and blame women

00:42:15.850 --> 00:42:16.850
and they all say,

00:42:17.850 --> 00:42:18.850
Well, the woman was the first one who sinned

00:42:19.850 --> 00:42:20.850
and the woman is the one because of her

00:42:21.850 --> 00:42:22.850
we are all astray and so on.

00:42:23.850 --> 00:42:24.850
There is no concrete evidence

00:42:25.850 --> 00:42:26.850
for that.

00:42:27.850 --> 00:42:28.850
Iblis said, Oh Adam, can I show you?

00:42:29.850 --> 00:42:30.850
Then Allah says,

00:42:31.850 --> 00:42:32.850
the two of them ate together.

00:42:33.850 --> 00:42:34.850
That is what Allah says.

00:42:35.850 --> 00:42:36.850
So why blame one the other?

00:42:37.850 --> 00:42:38.850
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:42:39.850 --> 00:42:40.850
the ability to take the blame

00:42:41.850 --> 00:42:42.850
when it is supposed to be on us.

00:42:43.850 --> 00:42:44.850
Because we all sometimes want to

00:42:45.850 --> 00:42:46.850
lay that buck on someone else.

00:42:47.850 --> 00:42:48.850
We learn from this that whenever

00:42:49.850 --> 00:42:50.850
it is our fault, just admit it.

00:42:51.850 --> 00:42:52.850
Don't try and pass the buck

00:42:53.850 --> 00:42:54.850
onto someone else just to blame them

00:42:55.850 --> 00:42:56.850
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:42:57.850 --> 00:42:58.850
they ate from that tree.

00:42:59.850 --> 00:43:00.850
And when they ate from the tree,

00:43:01.850 --> 00:43:02.850
do you want to know what happened?

00:43:03.850 --> 00:43:04.850
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:43:13.850 --> 00:43:14.850
Immediately as they ate,

00:43:15.850 --> 00:43:16.850
their private parts began to show

00:43:17.850 --> 00:43:19.850
and they ran to the trees of Jannah

00:43:20.850 --> 00:43:21.850
and the leaves of Jannah

00:43:22.850 --> 00:43:23.850
and they tried to cover themselves.

00:43:23.850 --> 00:43:24.850
Allah said moments ago

00:43:25.850 --> 00:43:26.850
that you will never be,

00:43:27.850 --> 00:43:28.850
you will never need clothing

00:43:29.850 --> 00:43:30.850
because your private parts will not show.

00:43:31.850 --> 00:43:32.850
And Allah says you will not need this

00:43:33.850 --> 00:43:34.850
and you will not need that.

00:43:35.850 --> 00:43:36.850
But once they ate from the tree,

00:43:37.850 --> 00:43:38.850
they began to feel the need

00:43:39.850 --> 00:43:40.850
to cover themselves.

00:43:41.850 --> 00:43:42.850
That was the first thing.

00:43:43.850 --> 00:43:44.850
They were now full of shame.

00:43:45.850 --> 00:43:46.850
They were ashamed of their deed,

00:43:47.850 --> 00:43:48.850
number one.

00:43:49.850 --> 00:43:50.850
And number two is they had to cover themselves.

00:43:51.850 --> 00:43:52.850
And then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:43:53.850 --> 00:43:54.850
says,

00:44:05.850 --> 00:44:09.850
Adam a.s. received certain words from Allah.

00:44:10.850 --> 00:44:11.850
So Allah forgave him after that.

00:44:12.850 --> 00:44:13.850
What were these words?

00:44:14.850 --> 00:44:15.850
Powerful words.

00:44:16.850 --> 00:44:18.850
The first time in the history of existence,

00:44:19.850 --> 00:44:21.850
someone was taught how to seek forgiveness.

00:44:21.850 --> 00:44:27.100
That act of worship known as tawbah and repentance.

00:44:28.100 --> 00:44:30.100
It was never ever engaged in before.

00:44:31.100 --> 00:44:32.100
No, never.

00:44:33.100 --> 00:44:34.100
Allah taught it to Adam first.

00:44:35.100 --> 00:44:37.100
This is when the angels were in shock once again.

00:44:38.100 --> 00:44:40.100
Now we see this is an act of worship

00:44:41.100 --> 00:44:42.100
that nobody has engaged in before.

00:44:43.100 --> 00:44:44.100
Allah taught Adam a.s. a few words.

00:44:45.100 --> 00:44:46.100
So he received those words

00:44:47.100 --> 00:44:48.100
and immediately he uttered the words.

00:44:49.100 --> 00:44:50.100
What did he say?

00:44:51.100 --> 00:44:52.100
He and his wife, both of them,

00:44:53.100 --> 00:44:54.100
The two of them said,

00:44:55.100 --> 00:44:56.100
O our Rabb, O our Rabb,

00:44:57.100 --> 00:44:58.100
we have oppressed ourselves.

00:44:59.100 --> 00:45:00.100
We have wronged ourselves.

00:45:01.100 --> 00:45:02.100
And if you are not going to have mercy on us,

00:45:03.100 --> 00:45:04.100
if you are not going to forgive us,

00:45:05.100 --> 00:45:06.100
we are going to be the losers, Ya Allah.

00:45:07.100 --> 00:45:08.100
So forgive us, Ya Allah.

00:45:09.100 --> 00:45:10.100
And Allah says,

00:45:11.100 --> 00:45:12.100
We forgave him immediately.

00:45:13.100 --> 00:45:14.100
What do we learn from this?

00:45:15.100 --> 00:45:16.100
We learn from this,

00:45:17.100 --> 00:45:20.140
there is man, one of the most powerful people

00:45:21.140 --> 00:45:22.140
in the world,

00:45:22.140 --> 00:45:23.140
we learn from this,

00:45:24.140 --> 00:45:25.140
there is man,

00:45:26.140 --> 00:45:27.140
one of the most powerful acts of worship

00:45:28.140 --> 00:45:29.140
that man can engage in,

00:45:30.140 --> 00:45:31.140
is istighfar,

00:45:32.140 --> 00:45:33.140
repentance,

00:45:34.140 --> 00:45:35.140
asking for forgiveness

00:45:36.140 --> 00:45:37.140
because that is what man was made for.

00:45:38.140 --> 00:45:39.140
Man was given the free will,

00:45:40.140 --> 00:45:41.140
but unlike the angels

00:45:42.140 --> 00:45:43.140
who do not have the ability to sin,

00:45:44.140 --> 00:45:45.140
man has the ability to sin,

00:45:46.140 --> 00:45:47.140
but he is asked to abstain from it

00:45:48.140 --> 00:45:49.140
and wherever he has fallen,

00:45:50.140 --> 00:45:51.140
he needs to immediately ask Allah's forgiveness.

00:45:52.140 --> 00:45:53.140
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:45:54.140 --> 00:45:55.140
O mankind, those of you

00:45:56.140 --> 00:45:57.140
who have oppressed against themselves,

00:45:58.140 --> 00:45:59.140
never lose hope in my mercy,

00:46:00.140 --> 00:46:01.140
I will forgive all your sins.

00:46:02.140 --> 00:46:03.140
All that is required is for us to ask

00:46:04.140 --> 00:46:05.140
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to forgive us.

00:46:06.140 --> 00:46:07.140
So it's important we learn the lesson.

00:46:08.140 --> 00:46:09.140
There are four things required

00:46:10.140 --> 00:46:11.140
when we want to ask Allah's forgiveness.

00:46:12.140 --> 00:46:13.140
Firstly, to admit the sin.

00:46:14.140 --> 00:46:15.140
Secondly, to regret over it.

00:46:16.140 --> 00:46:18.140
Thirdly, to ask Allah to forgive it.

00:46:19.140 --> 00:46:21.140
And fourthly, to promise that we will not do it again.

00:46:22.140 --> 00:46:23.140
When conditions are met,

00:46:24.140 --> 00:46:25.140
nobody needs to know your sin,

00:46:26.140 --> 00:46:27.140
not a single soul.

00:46:28.140 --> 00:46:29.140
Between you and Allah, it is wiped out.

00:46:30.140 --> 00:46:31.140
Don't have a doubt in your heart

00:46:32.140 --> 00:46:33.140
and in your mind.

00:46:34.140 --> 00:46:35.140
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:46:36.140 --> 00:46:37.140
the ability to understand those four conditions

00:46:38.140 --> 00:46:39.140
and may He make us from those who can fulfill it.

00:46:40.140 --> 00:46:41.140
Insha'Allah we will continue tomorrow

00:46:42.140 --> 00:46:43.140
and insha'Allah we ask Allah to forgive us

00:46:44.140 --> 00:46:45.140
our sins and we ask Allah to open our doors

00:46:46.140 --> 00:46:47.140
until we meet again with the continuation

00:46:48.140 --> 00:46:49.140
we say,

00:46:49.140 --> 00:46:50.140
Subhanallah wa bihamdihi

00:46:51.140 --> 00:46:52.140
Subhanaka Allahumma wa bihamdik

00:46:53.140 --> 00:46:54.140
We witness that there is no god but You.

00:46:55.140 --> 00:46:56.140
We ask Your forgiveness and repent to Him.
